This paper discusses distributional semantics, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the theoretical status of distributional semantics within a broader theory of language and cognition, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the relationship between distributional semantics and formal semantics, which could fall under computational complexity (cs.CC) or cryptography and security (cs.CR).
